per. Mix well.\n6. Pour the yogurt sauce over the eggplant and turkey layers, making sure it covers them evenly.\n\n7. Bake for 30-40 minutes, or until the sauce is set and golden brown.\n\n8. Let the Moussaka cool for 10 minutes before serving. Garnish with extra chopped fresh dill, if desired. \n\n**Tips:**\n\n* To save time, you can broil the eggplant slices instead of baking them.  \n* For a richer flavor, add a tablespoon of tomato paste to the turkey filling.\n* Use a combination of different spices, such as cumin, paprika, or cayenne pepper, to adjust the flavor profile to your liking.\n\nEnjoy this healthy and delicious take on the classic Greek dish! \n\n\n"
