et over medium heat. Remove the chicken from the marinade, reserving the marinade. Grill or pan-fry the chicken pieces for 5-7 minutes per side, or until cooked through and golden brown. \n6. **Assemble the Tikka Masala:**  Add the cooked chicken pieces to the sauce. Stir to combine.\n7.  Simmer for 5 minutes, or until the chicken is heated through and the flavors have melded. \n8. Serve hot over basmati rice, garnished with fresh cilantro and a dollop of plain yogurt, if desired.\n\n**Tips:**\n\n* To make a vegan version, substitute the chicken with firm tofu, marinated in the same spice blend.\n*  For a richer sauce, add a tablespoon of tomato paste to the sauce while it’s simmering.\n*  Adjust the amount of spices to your preference, especially the cayenne pepper. \n*  Serve with naan bread, rice, or other Indian breads for a complete meal.\n\nEnjoy this flavorful and satisfying Chicken Tikka Masala!"
