ews, coconut milk, coconut oil, and vanilla extract in a blender or food processor. \n4. Blend until smooth and creamy, scraping down the sides as needed. \n\n**Prepare the Dark Chocolate Drizzle:**\n\n1. Place the dark chocolate chips and coconut oil in a heatproof bowl set over a saucepan of simmering water. Stir until melted and smooth. \n\n**Assemble and Serve:**\n\n1. Once the bread is cool, slice it and spread with the toasted cashew-coconut butter.\n2. Drizzle the melted dark chocolate over the top.\n\nEnjoy this delicious and wholesome banana bread!\n\n**Tips:**\n\n*  For a sweeter bread, add 1/4 cup (50g) of brown sugar to the batter along with the granulated sugar.\n*  Use other nuts, such as almonds or pecans, in place of cashews for the butter.\n*  For a richer flavor, substitute full-fat coconut milk for the unsweetened version. \n*  Feel free to add additional toppings, like chopped nuts, shredded coconut, or fresh berries."
