aked eggplant slices, overlapping them slightly. Repeat the layers, ending with eggplant.\n\n5. **Make the Creamy Cashew Sauce:** In a blender or food processor, combine the soaked cashews, water, lemon juice, nutritional yeast, garlic, olive oil, salt, and pepper. Blend until smooth and creamy, adding a little more water if needed.\n\n6. Pour the cashew sauce over the eggplant and chicken layers, making sure it covers them evenly. \n\n7. Bake for 30-40 minutes, or until the sauce is set and golden brown. \n\n8. Let the Moussaka cool for 10 minutes before serving. Garnish with extra chopped fresh dill, if desired. \n\n**Tips:**\n\n* For a richer flavor, add a tablespoon of tomato paste to the chicken filling.\n* You can use a combination of spices to adjust the flavor profile to your liking, such as cumin, paprika, or cayenne pepper.\n*  For a more rustic presentation, top with a sprinkle of toasted pine nuts.\n\nEnjoy this delicious, dairy-free, and egg-free Moussaka!"
