n sugar, lime juice, sesame oil, and red pepper flakes (if using) in a small bowl until smooth and well combined.\n2. **Heat the oil:**  Heat olive oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat. Add the chicken strips and cook until lightly browned, about 3 minutes per side. Remove the chicken and set aside.\n3. **Cook the vegetables:** Add bean sprouts, cabbage, bok choy, onions, and garlic to the skillet and cook for 3-4 minutes, or until the vegetables are softened and lightly browned. \n4.  **Reintroduce the chicken:** Return the cooked chicken to the skillet. Pour the sauce over the ingredients and stir to combine. Cook for 2 minutes, or until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is heated through. \n5. **Assemble:** Divide the cooked noodles among two bowls. Top with the chicken pad see ew mixture and sprinkle with chopped green onions. \n\n**Tips:**\n\n*  You can add other vegetables to the stir-fry, such as snow peas, carrots, or bell peppers. \n* For a vegan version, use a plant-based alternative to fish sauce, or simply omit it.\n*  If you like, add a pinch of cayenne pepper to the sauce for a touch of heat.\n*  Serve with a side of lime wedges or sriracha sauce for an extra flavor boost.\n\nEnjoy this flavorful and satisfying chicken pad see ew!\n\n\n## Chicken Enchiladas\n\nThis recipe features tortillas filled with seasoned chicken, cheese, and a creamy sauce, then baked until bubbly and delicious.\n\n**Yields:** 6-8 enchiladas\n\n**Nutritional Information per serving (approximate):**\n\n* Calories: 350 kcal\n* Protein: 25g\n* Carbohydrates: 35g\n* Fat: 10g\n\n**Ingredients:**\n\n* **For the Filling:**\n    * 1 tbsp (15 ml) olive oil\n    * 1 onion, chopped\n    * 2 cloves garlic, minced\n    * 1 tsp chili powder\n    * 1/2 tsp cumin\n    * 1/4 tsp salt\n    * 1/4 tsp black pepper\n    * 500g boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cooked and shredded\n    * 1 (400g) can diced tomatoes, undrained\n    * 1/2 cup (120 ml) chicken broth\n    * 1/2 cup (120 ml) light cream\n* **For the Sauce:**\n    * 1/2 cup (120ml) tomato sauce \n    * 1/4 cup (60ml) water\n    * 1 tbsp (15ml) chili powder\n    * 1/2 tsp cumin\n    * 1/4 tsp salt\n    * 1/4 tsp black pepper\n* **For Assembling:**\n    * 6-8 corn or flour tortillas \n    * 1/2 cup (120g) shredded cheese (cheddar, Monterey Jack, or Colby Jack work well)\n\n**Instructions:**\n\n1. **Prepare the Filling:** Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add onion and garlic and cook until softened, about 5 minutes. \n2. Stir in chili powder, cumin, salt, and pepper. Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. \n3. Add the shredded chicken, diced tomatoes, and chicken broth. Bring to a simmer and cook for 5 minutes, or until the sauce has thickened slightly. \n4. Stir in the light cream.  \n5. **Prepare the Sauce:**  Combine tomato sauce, water, chili powder, cumin, salt, and pepper in a small saucepan. Bring to a simmer and cook for 5 minutes. \n6. **Assemble the Enchiladas:** Preheat oven to 180°C. Warm the tortillas slightly in a microwave or skillet, then fill each tortilla with a heaping spoonful of the chicken filling. Sprinkle with cheese. \n7. Roll up the tortillas and place them seam-down in a greased 9x13 inch baking dish. \n8. Pour the tomato sauce over the enchiladas, making sure to cover them evenly. \n9.  Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly. \n\n**Tips:**\n\n*  You can add other vegetables to the filling, like bell peppers, onions, or corn. \n*  If you prefer a spicier filling, add a pinch of cayenne pepper. \n*  Serve with a side of sour cream, guacamole, or salsa. \n\nEnjoy these delicious chicken enchiladas!"
