 minute, stirring constantly, to release the aromas. \n4. Add the diced tomatoes, coconut milk, and vegetable broth. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 10 minutes. \n5. Add the marinated beef to the pot. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 - 2 hours, or until the beef is very tender and the sauce has reduced significantly. \n6.  Add 1/2 cup (120ml) water and simmer for an additional 15-20 minutes, or until the sauce has thickened to a rich and glossy consistency.\n7. Serve hot over basmati rice, garnished with chopped cilantro.\n\n**Tips:**\n\n*  You can use a different type of beef, such as flank steak or chuck steak, but make sure it's a cut suitable for slow cooking.\n*  Adjust the amount of spices to your preference, especially the cayenne pepper. \n* For a deeper flavor, toast the spices (curry powder, cumin, coriander, turmeric, cinnamon) in a dry skillet over medium heat for a few minutes before adding them to the pot.\n* Serve with a side of steamed rice or flatbread, such as roti or naan.\n\nEnjoy this rich and flavorful beef rendang!\n\n\n## Lomo Saltado (Peruvian Beef Stir-Fry)\n\nThis dish features tender strips of beef stir-fried with onions, tomatoes, soy sauce, and a touch of vinegar, creating a savory and vibrant meal.\n\n**Yields:** 2 servings\n\n**Nutritional Information per serving (approximate):**\n\n* Calories: 550 kcal\n* Protein: 35g\n* Carbohydrates: 60g\n* Fat: 20g\n\n**Ingredients:**\n\n* 1 tbsp (15 ml) olive oil\n* 200g sirloin steak, thinly sliced\n* 1 large onion, thinly sliced\n* 2 cloves garlic, minced\n* 1 (400g) can diced tomatoes, undrained\n* 1/4 cup (60ml) soy sauce\n* 1 tbsp (15ml) rice vinegar\n* 1 tsp (5ml) sugar\n* 1/2 tsp (2.5g) cumin\n* 1/4 tsp black pepper\n* 1/4 cup chopped cilantro (for garnish)\n* 200g cooked rice (or your favorite side dish)\n\n**Instructions:**\n\n1. Heat olive oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook until browned on both sides, about 2-3 minutes per side. Remove beef from the skillet and set aside.\n2. Add the onion and garlic to the skillet and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.\n3. Stir in diced tomatoes, soy sauce, rice vinegar, sugar, cumin, and black pepper. Bring to a simmer and cook for 5 minutes, allowing the sauce to thicken slightly.\n4. Return the beef to the skillet. Stir to combine. \n5. Cook for an additional 2 minutes, or until the beef is heated through and the sauce is glossy.\n6. Serve immediately over rice, garnished with chopped cilantro. \n\n**Tips:**\n\n* For a spicier dish, add a pinch of red pepper flakes to the sauce.\n*  Feel free to use other cuts of beef, such as flank steak or skirt steak. \n* Serve Lomo Saltado with french fries for a traditional Peruvian accompaniment.\n\nEnjoy this vibrant and flavorful Peruvian stir-fry!\n\n\n## Beef Kefta Kebabs (Middle Eastern Beef Skewers)\n\nThese skewers feature ground beef flavored with spices and herbs, then grilled to perfection. They are a popular dish in the Middle East and can be served with various accompaniments.\n\n**Yields:** 4 servings\n\n**Nutritional Information per serving (approximate):**\n\n* Calories: 350 kcal\n* Protein: 30g\n* Carbohydrates: 20g\n* Fat: 15g\n\n**Ingredients:**\n\n* **For the Kefta:**\n    * 500g ground beef\n    * 1 large onion, finely chopped\n    * 2 cloves garlic, minced\n    * 1 tbsp (15ml) chopped fresh parsley\n    * 1 tbsp (15ml) chopped fresh mint\n    * 1 tsp (5g) ground cumin\n    * 1/2 tsp (2.5g) ground coriander\n    * 1/4 tsp salt\n    * 1/4 tsp black pepper\n* **For the Marinade:**\n    * 1/4 cup (60ml) plain yogurt\n    * 1 tbsp (15ml) lemon juice\n* **For Serving:**\n    * 4 skewers (metal or wooden)\n    * 1 tbsp olive oil\n    * 1/2 cup (120ml) hummus\n    * 1/4 cup (60ml) chopped fresh parsley\n    * 2 pita bread\n    * 1 tbsp tahini sauce\n\n**Instructions:**\n\n1. **Prepare the Kefta:**  Combine the ground beef, onion, garlic, parsley, mint, cumin, coriander, salt, and pepper in a large bowl. Mix well using your hands until everything is evenly combined.\n2. **Marinate:**  Pour the yogurt and lemon juice over the mixture and stir well to coat evenly. Marinate in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes, or up to 4 hours. \n3. **Assemble the Kebabs:**  Form the marinated beef mixture into 4 equal portions and shape them into elongated kebabs.  Thread them onto the skewers. \n4. **Cook the Kebabs:** Heat the olive oil in a grill pan or skillet over medium heat. Cook the kebabs for 4-5 minutes per side, or until browned and cooked through. \n5. **Serve:**  Serve the cooked kebabs with hummus, chopped fresh parsley, pita bread, and tahini sauce.\n\n**Tips:**\n\n*  You can add other spices to the kefta mixture, such as paprika, cayenne pepper, or turmeric. \n*  For a vegetarian version, substitute the ground beef with a mixture of ground lentils and breadcrumbs. \n*  Serve with other Middle Eastern accompaniments, such as baba ghanoush, tabbouleh, or roasted vegetables.\n\nEnjoy these flavorful and aromatic beef kefta kebabs!"
