ar\n    * 1/2 cup (60g) unsweetened cocoa powder \n    * 1/2 tsp vanilla extract \n    * 1/2 tsp instant coffee granules \n    * 60g almond flour \n    * 30g oat flour\n    * 1/4 tsp baking powder\n    * 1/4 tsp salt\n* **For the Salty Tahini Caramel:**\n    * 60 ml tahini\n    * 15 ml coconut oil\n    * 30 ml maple syrup\n    * 2.5g sea salt \n\n**Instructions:**\n\n1. **Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).** Grease a 20 x 20 cm square baking pan.\n2. **Prepare the Brownie:**  In a large bowl, combine the grated cauliflower, almond milk, melted coconut oil, sugar, cocoa powder, vanilla extract, and coffee granules. Mix well to combine.\n3. In a separate bowl, whisk together the almond flour, oat flour, baking powder, and salt.\n4.  Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. Don't overmix.\n5.  Pour the batter into the prepared pan and spread evenly.\n6. Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with a few moist crumbs.\n7. Let the brownie cool completely in the pan before cutting into squares.\n\n**Prepare the Salty Tahini Caramel:**\n\n1. While the brownie is baking, prepare the caramel. In a small saucepan, combine the tahini, coconut oil, maple syrup, and sea salt. \n2. Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the caramel is smooth and bubbly, about 2-3 minutes.\n3. Remove from heat and let cool slightly.\n\n**Assemble and Serve:**\n\n1. Once the brownie is cool, top with the salty tahini caramel.\n\nEnjoy this delicious and healthy cauliflower brownie!\n\n##  Honest Greens-Inspired Macadamia Miso Cheesecake (Plant-Based)\n\n* **Yields:** 8-10 servings \n\n**Ingredients:**\n\n* **For the Crust:** \n    * 150g almond flour\n    * 1/2 cup (120g) shredded coconut flakes\n    * 1/4 cup (60ml) melted coconut oil\n    * 2 tbsp (30 ml) maple syrup\n    * 1/4 tsp salt\n* **For the Filling:**\n    * 200g macadamia nuts, soaked in hot water for 30 minutes, then drained\n    * 1/2 cup (120ml) unsweetened almond milk \n    * 1/4 cup (60 ml) lemon juice\n    * 1 tbsp (15 ml) white miso paste\n    * 1/2 cup (100g) granulated sugar\n    * 1/2 tsp vanilla extract \n    * 1/4 tsp sea salt \n* **For the Topping:**\n    * 1 cup (240 ml) mixed berries\n    * 1 tbsp (15ml) maple syrup \n\n**Instructions:**\n\n1. **Prepare the Crust:** Preheat oven to 175°C (350°F). Lightly grease a 20 cm springform pan.  \n2.  In a food processor, combine the almond flour, coconut flakes, melted coconut oil, maple syrup, and salt. Pulse until a crumbly crust forms. Press the mixture into the bottom of the prepared pan. Bake for 10-12 minutes, or until lightly golden brown.\n3. **Prepare the Filling:**  In a blender or food processor, combine the soaked macadamia nuts, almond milk, lemon juice, miso paste, sugar, vanilla extract, and salt. Blend until completely smooth and creamy. \n4. Pour the filling over the cooled crust.\n5. Bake for 30-35 minutes, or until the cheesecake is set around the edges but still slightly jiggly in the center.  \n6. Let cool completely on a wire rack before topping.\n7. **Prepare the Topping:**  Combine the berries and maple syrup in a small bowl.\n8.  Top the cooled cheesecake with the berry mixture. \n9. Serve chilled.\n\n**Tips:**\n\n* You can substitute the macadamia nuts with cashews or pecans for a variation in flavor.\n*  Use a vegan white chocolate or a dairy-free whipped topping (or a whipped coconut cream) for a more decadent topping. \n\nEnjoy this delicious and healthy cheesecake!\n\nRemember to adjust the ingredients and recipes to your taste preference and dietary needs! Enjoy creating these delicious and healthier treats!"
