option that's both decadent and guilt-free. \n\n**Yields:** 12 cookies\n\n**Ingredients:**\n\n* 1/2 cup (120 ml) unsweetened almond milk \n* 1/4 cup (60 ml) melted coconut oil \n* 1/2 cup (100g) granulated sugar\n* 1/4 cup (50g) unsweetened cocoa powder\n* 1/2 tsp vanilla extract \n* 1/2 tsp baking powder \n* 1/4 tsp salt\n* 1/2 cup (60g) almond flour\n* 1/4 cup (30g) oat flour \n* 1/4 cup (40g) dark chocolate chips\n\n**Instructions:**\n\n1. Preheat oven to 175°C (350°F).  Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. \n2. In a large bowl, whisk together almond milk, melted coconut oil, sugar, cocoa powder, and vanilla extract.\n3.  In a separate bowl, whisk together almond flour, oat flour, baking powder, and salt.\n4.  Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. \n5. Stir in chocolate chips.\n6.  Drop by rounded tablespoons onto the prepared baking sheet.\n7.  Bake for 12-15 minutes, or until the edges are set and the centers are just slightly soft. \n8. Let the cookies cool on the baking sheet for a few minutes before transferring them to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\n##  Honest Greens-Inspired Honest \"Red Velvet\" Cupcake (Plant-Based)\n\nThis recipe is a plant-based take on the classic red velvet cupcake, featuring a moist and tender crumb with a creamy vegan frosting. \n\n**Yields:** 4-6 cupcakes \n\n**Ingredients:**\n\n**For the Cupcake:**\n\n* 1/2 cup (120ml) unsweetened almond milk\n* 1/4 cup (60ml) melted coconut oil\n* 1/2 cup (100g) granulated sugar\n* 1/4 cup (50g) unsweetened cocoa powder\n* 1/4 cup (60ml) beetroot purée (from cooked beets) \n* 1 tsp vanilla extract\n* 1/2 tsp baking powder \n* 1/4 tsp baking soda\n* 1/4 tsp salt\n* 1/2 cup (60g) almond flour\n* 1/4 cup (30g) oat flour\n\n**For the Frosting:**\n\n* 1/2 cup (120ml) vegan cream cheese or a cashew cream cheese alternative\n* 1/4 cup (60 ml) vegan butter, softened\n* 1/2 cup (100g) powdered sugar \n* 1/2 tsp vanilla extract\n* 1 tbsp beetroot purée (for a touch of color)\n\n**Instructions:**\n\n1. **Preheat oven to 175°C (350°F).** Line a muffin tin with paper liners. \n2. **Prepare the Cupcake:**  In a large bowl, whisk together the almond milk, melted coconut oil, sugar, cocoa powder, beetroot purée, and vanilla extract until smooth.\n3. In a separate bowl, whisk together the almond flour, oat flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\n4. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. Don't overmix. \n5. Spoon the batter into the prepared muffin tins. \n6. Bake for 18-22 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. \n7. Let the cupcakes cool completely in the muffin tin before transferring them to a wire rack to cool. \n8. **Prepare the Frosting:**  In a bowl, cream together the vegan cream cheese and vegan butter until smooth. \n9. Gradually add the powdered sugar, vanilla extract, and beetroot purée (for a touch of color), mixing until smooth and light. \n10.  Frost the cooled cupcakes with the frosting.\n\n**Tips:**\n\n* You can add a splash of red food coloring to the batter for a deeper red hue.\n* If you want a more intense beetroot flavor, use more beet purée in the frosting or batter. \n\nEnjoy these delicious and healthier treats! \n\nRemember, this is just a guide, feel free to adjust the ingredients and amounts based on your preferences and dietary needs!"
